<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="1066" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="22.[163,780,634,779]" pageId="22" pageNumber="1066">
<emphasis box="[163,311,634,656]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="1066">Etymology:</emphasis>
The name is derived from River Guadarrama, a river with a name of Arabic roots: 
<emphasis box="[716,773,665,686]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="1066">wadi</emphasis>
, river, and 
<emphasis box="[282,376,696,717]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="1066">ar-rama</emphasis>
, sandy. We propose this name as a reference to the 
<typeStatus box="[341,390,727,748]" pageId="22" pageNumber="1066">type</typeStatus>
locality in ‘Sierra de Guadarrama’, a mountain range named after this river.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
